		<part part_index="2" name="Hurricane facts" page="0" source="2">
      	<article allWordsNum="98">
            	<![CDATA[
A hurricane (飓风) is a huge storm. Each hurricane usually lasts for over a week. It moves 10 to 20 miles per hour over the ocean.
Hurricanes get heat and energy through warm ocean waters. They rotate (旋转) in a counter-clockwise direction (逆时针方向) around an "eye" —the center of the hurricane—in the Northern Hemisphere (北半球), and in a clockwise direction (顺时针方向) in the Southern Hemisphere.
The "eye" of the storm is the calmest part. It has only light winds and fair weather. When hurricanes come onto land, the heavy rain, strong winds and large waves can damage buildings, trees and cars.
	]]>
            </article>
